 **** Merging Branches in Git ***

Steps to be followed:
1.	Create a new branch
2.	Create a new file in the new branch
3.	Switch to the main branch
4.	Merge the branches
5.	Push the changes to the remote repository


1. Create a new branch
      $ mkdir project           ( Create a directory )
      $ cd project              ( Change Directory )
      $ git branch New_Branch   ( Create new branch )    
      $ git branch              ( Verify new branch created )
      
2. Create a new file in the new branch
      $ git checkout New_Branch
      $ touch file1.txt
      $ git add file1.txt
      $git commit -m "File added"
      
3.  Switch to the main branch
      $ git checkout main
      $ git branch

4. Merge the branches
      $ git merge New_Branch 
         
5. Push the changes to the remote repository
      $ git push -u origin main
      
      
*** Go to the remote repository to check whether the branch is updated ***
